---
interface Props {
  stateAgencyAbbreviation: string;
}

const { stateAgencyAbbreviation } = Astro.props;
---

<aside
  class="my-12 rounded-lg border border-disclaimer-border bg-disclaimer-bg/40 p-6"
  aria-labelledby="reassurance-heading"
>
  <h2 id="reassurance-heading" class="!mt-0">What you're actually paying for (and what we don't touch)</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed">
    Targeting elder caregivers is a magnet for scams. Here is exactly what we do, what we don't, and what stays in
    your control:
  </p>
  <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
    <li>
      <strong>You stay in full control of the trust and the money.</strong> Your trustee opens the account and manages
      the funds. We never see, hold, or touch a dollar of your family's income.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>We never contact your parent.</strong> We don't collect their name, income, Social Security number,
      address, or any other detail about them. The only data we hold is the email you give us at checkout.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Your email is never sold or shared.</strong> Not to attorneys, not to Medicaid planners, not to
      lead-generation outfits. <a href="/privacy">Read the privacy policy.</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>We earn no kickbacks.</strong> No attorney referral fees, no affiliate links, no advertising. Our only
      revenue is the $79 you pay for the kit.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Every claim cites {stateAgencyAbbreviation} directly.</strong> If you find anything on this page that
      doesn't match what {stateAgencyAbbreviation} publishes, email us and we'll correct it within five business days.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Money back if {stateAgencyAbbreviation} rejects the QIT</strong> for any reason traceable to following the
      kit. One business day, no fight.
    </li>
  </ul>
</aside>
